terms in
the right-hand side of ()), but its explicit 
form is not
important for our purposes here(The only 
important
property of this term is that this is a gauge 
transformation with
some gauge parameter 

. Explicit gauge fixing 
procedure for
the equation () becomes important in higher 
orders of
curvature expansion and it is presented in much detail 
in
